<F P=103> AU0401184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES 4/1/1994 -- Romania's President 
Ion Iliescu received on January 4, 1994, a delegation of the 
North [as received] Korean Daewoo group, led by Kim U-chung, 
chairman of the administration board. 
  The Daewoo group intends to explore ways for large-scale 
investments in Romania in the car-making industry, 
ship-building, refineries, electronics, tourism and the 
financial-banking sector. 
  President Iliescu saluted the interest of South Korean 
businessmen in cooperation actions in Romania and told his guest 
about the potentialities of the Romanian economy, the 
opportunities created for foreign investors by the Romanian 
legislation. The Romanian president encouraged the 
representives of the Daewoo group to have contacts with Romanian 
businessmen in view of making mutually advantageous transactions. 

</TEXT>

