  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 18/4/1994 -- "The talks between 
the foreign ministers of Romania and Armenia pointed to the 
necessity of concluding the soonest a basic political treaty 
between the two countries," said Romanian Foreign Ministry 
Spokesman Mircea Geoana at the close of the first round of talks 
between Teodor Melescanu and Vahan Papazyan. It is hoped that 
in a near future that important document will be signed during a 
meeting of the two countries' presidents. 
